                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>Text I-1 includes the hymns:</note>
                     <note>- ʾO-ʾǝgzǝʾtǝyä qǝddǝst dǝngǝl Maryam Mariham ʾǝmmu lä-ʾIyäsus kähali ... "O my Lady, Holy Virgin Mary, Mother of Jesus the Almighty ..." (fol. 9rb-va) (cp. ChRep no. 373)</note>
                     <note>- Sälam läki ʾo-ʾǝgzǝʾtǝyä Maryam dǝngǝl ʾǝmmä mädḫǝn wä-ʾǝmmä bǝrhan ... "Salutation to you, o my Lady, Virgin Mary, Mother of the Saviour and Mother of the Light ..." (fols. 9va-10rb).</note>
                     <note/>
                     <note>Most of the miracles of Mary (Text I-4) are numbered. The numbers 7 and 8 were not used; the numbers 27-29 (fols. 43va-48rb) and 37 (fol. 54ra-va) were used twice. The last miracle in quire VIII is numbered as 51 (hand a). Quire IX, written in hand b, includes eight miracles, from which four are numbered as 39-42. Consequently, hand b continues the numbering on quire X starting with number 60 (fol. 70vb).</note>
                     <note/>
                     <note>The first miracle is followed by a short hymn: Sobä ṣäḥafä Däqsǝyos täʾamriha ʾǝludä ... "When Däqsǝyos wrote the collection of her miracles ..." (fol. 10rb)</note>
                     <note/>
                     <note>Text I-5 comprises 20 strophes which are strophes 2-21 according to GrohHymn pp. 336-47.</note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="coloph1">
